# 2p_sync_aurora — CLIENT. Pairs with 2p_sync_aurora.host.shot.
#
# Stationary observer ~120 px to the right of the host's spawn so
# the host walks INTO the client's camera view. Burst captures over
# the SAME tick range as the host so frames can be compared 1:1.
#
# What we're looking for in the client's burst frames:
#   * Smooth motion of the host's mech (no jitter / shaking)
#   * Jet plume appears at the same moment as the host's view
#   * Slope pose looks like the host's view (legs tracking surface)
#   * Apex of the running-jet matches the host's apex

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/2p_sync_aurora.client
network connect 127.0.0.1:24500
name ClientB
loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Sidearm" Light Standard
map aurora
no_parallax
# Position is set server-side by the host's `peer_spawn 1 ...`;
# our local spawn_at would be overridden by the next snapshot.
aim 2000 2700

# Stay still — no inputs. The camera tracks our stationary mech, and
# the host walks through frame as it climbs the western slope.
burst client_t from 200 to 460 every 6

at 540 end

contact_sheet client_sheet cols 8 cell 320 180
